column5: Fished Rice today from 8:30am to 12:30pm managed 7 eyes from 17 to 25 inches, kept the 2 smaller ones at 17 and 19 inches, the rest smiled and went back to the 7 to 10 feet of water where they were caught. water was 62 degrees today, and was 56 on tuesday I got scrubbed on tuesday except for one oos bucket, all fish caught on bucktails, tried rubber and cranks with no luck so I went back to bucktails
7 walleye sounds like a good day of fishing to me...  nice going
